who_heading: Tech is hard, governing is harder - Lend a hand!
---
who_body:

The most important office in a democracy is the office of the citizen. To tackle today's problems, we need everyone on deck. That means activiating developers, journalists, user experiance researchers, breaucrats, data scientests, social service workers, and curious citizens to help us.  
---
who_title_1: Neighbors 
---
who_description_1:

Government is simply the name we give to the things we choose to do together. Tackling these challenges really does require everyone.  
---
who_title_2: Public Servants
---
who_description_2:

We believe in breaucrats. The best civic technology builds apps that support public servents and are built around their needs and challegnes.
---
who_title_3: Designers
---
who_description_3:

If nobody understands what they're seeing, then the project is useless. Designers help us create projecs that are easy to use and understand.
---
who_title_4: Developers
---
who_description_4:

Use your skills to develop solutions that can help solve big problems.
---
who_title_5: Data Scientists 
---
who_description_5:

Use your skills to help understand the data and help people understand what's going on and how we can fix it. 
